profile_positions.description:
- Formulate budget estimates for several subsidiary companies in support of the company’s objectives;
- Develop plans to allocate company’s monthly resources and monitor the program execution;
- Analyze various project and business proposals (especially in the field of renewable energy, plantation, and housing development) to further develop and expand the company’s wide-ranging investments;
- Prepare monthly report for several subsidiary companies and provide analysis of monthly happenings and events;
- Review and interpret accounting and financial management policy, procedures, standards and statutes to ensure subsidiary companies’ compliance;
- Provide recommendations based on findings that identify cost savings through improved operations in the field;

- Provide technical input in drafting the concept and framework for Trust Fund, including providing relevant information to  to achieve expected results on trust fund as funding modality;
- Perform  desk review of trust fund case studies at country, regional and global level and examination different models of the Trust Fund with specific reference on: 
• Administering and governance structure (e.g., steering committees, decision- making bodies, policy/guidance mechanisms, and membership)
• Accountability measures and monitoring and reporting framework and systems, including actual performance against the framework.
• Legal framework and documentation (TOR, MOUs, LOAs, grant agreements, etc.)
• Support the monitoring of grant implementation, results and evaluate effectiveness of the A4DES program, including proposing adjustments if needed;
- Facilitate  meetings, interviews and consultations with Government agencies, development partners, private sector and the civil society organizations (CSO);
- Draft and write reports that address the strategic and policy issues relating to the use of funds, and findings and recommendations for future action for the trust fund in Indonesia, with particular focus on immediate establishment of nationally managed trust fund for A4DES
- Provide necessary supports to WG DFM on critical issues facing the Working Groups and seek solutions on trust fund matters; 
- Other tasks, as required

- Support and assist in the comprehensive selection of proposals for the MCC compact program in accordance with the predetermined MCC and MC-Indonesia Steering Committee (SC) guidelines by working closely at the project level with the chosen concept paper proposers and related stakeholders;
- Supervise and evaluate the final 13 submitted concept papers that have been selected through a series of compact development process by providing in-depth and constructive analysis report to the draft proposals to ensure that they are in compliance with the MCC guidelines as well as the ADB constraint analysis for Indonesia;
- Prepare MCC compact program-specific briefs, checklists, and progress presentations to be presented before the MC-Indonesia Steering Committee (SC);
- Analyze and prepare brief on the economic and beneficiary impact of the concept papers in accordance with the MCC Guidelines for Economic and Beneficiary Analysis; hence assuring that the proposed concept papers have already met the selection indicators and the main “poverty reduction” theme as set by the MCC;
- Prepare detailed Concept Paper Matrix Reviews and Concept Paper Digest Reviews to systematically monitor and evaluate each section of the compact papers and recommend ways in which the proposals can be improved to address the “poverty reduction through sustainable economic growth” theme of the program;
- Identify potential problems in the implementation of, and conflicting data, structure, and/or concept in the proposed concept papers and propose solutions to ensure the sustainability of the compact development process;
- Prepare MC-Indonesia compact program-specific briefs, checklists, and progress presentations to be presented before the MC-Indonesia Steering Committee (SC);
- Conduct an actual field visits to various concept paper proposers to monitor and evaluate the validity and reliability of the proposals.

- Develop and revise the final draft of Timor-Leste Strategic Development Plan (SDP) Report for the year 2010 to 2030 to be submitted to the Prime Minister’s Office and the National Parliament of Timor-Leste;
- Assist in the development of Timor-Leste’s long-term sector budget allocation based on Government Budget Plan for the year 2009 and 2010 to subsequently produce the long-term macroeconomic model;
- Perform data collection, research, develop, and analyze key economic information and develop Timor-Leste’s budget resource envelope based on the aforesaid macroeconomic model by taking into account the proposed long-term sector plan (the SDP Investment Package) and the Ordinary Capital Expenditures of the Government of the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste to produce the Macroeconomic Framework section of the SDP report for the period of 2010 to 2030;
- Assist in the drafting and writing of the Macroeconomic Framework section of the SDP Report by incorporating the long-term sector plans prepared by other sector specialists utilizing the data and policy framework proposed by the sector ministries of the Government of the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste through an all-inclusive inter-agency consultative process;
- Assist the Team Leader in coordinating other sector specialists and assure quality control of the final Timor-Leste SDP Report by, among other things, confirming the validity and consistency of the data, statistics, figures, and assumptions stipulated in the report;
- Draft, edit in, or translate the individual sector reports prepared by other sector specialists into English and/or Indonesian to produce the Timor-Leste SDP Report in the two languages while ensuring the consistency and reliability of the contents;
- Prepare the Executive Summary and progress presentation of the SDP Report to be presented before the Prime Minister of Timor-Leste and his line ministries.

- Assist the team leader and other technical consultants in preparing a thorough basis for the drafting and writing of technical analysis and review of the Public - Private Partnership (PPP) projects handled by TAS-IRSDP from the economics and financial standpoint to ensure feasibility, including but not limited to cost-recovery, bankability, and sustainability of the PPP projects throughout the entire concession period;
- Assist in the development of Multi Criteria Analysis (MCA) for TAS-IRSDP to better prioritize PPP projects based on the relevant criteria weighting (i.e., Market Demand, Financial Feasibility, Land Availability, Sector Framework, Availability of Project Gazzete, and Environmental Impacts);
- Perform data collection, literature review, and international best practice case study analysis on the terms and conditions and the nature of various donor countries/agencies to assist in financing for PPP projects in Indonesia;
- Provide inputs and analysis to, and direct consultations with the project consultants in the Pre-Feasibility (Pre-FS) stage alongside other sector specialists at TAS-IRSDP to ensure that the proposed PPP projects have already met the required due diligence for PPP projects provision;
- Evaluate the overall Pre-Feasibility Study (Pre-FS) Report prepared by project consultants with focus on: (1) Economics Analysis through a comprehensive constructive criticisms on the projected Social Cost-Benefit Analysis (SCBA) of the PPP projects and by confirming the claimed “with and without project” net benefits; and (2) Financial Analysis by exercising various scenarios in the financial model (e.g., variation in tariffs, business volume, interest rate, debt-equity ratio, etc.) in order to achieve financial feasibility of the projects (i.e., by comparing the projects’ FIRR, ROE, NPV, DSCR, among others, with the predetermined benchmarks) for the national PPP projects which fall under the Project Development Facility (PDF) Fund;
- etc.

- Assist in the multi-faceted preparation of Tender Pre-Qualification (PQ) of Tanah Ampo Cruise Terminal Project;
- Assist in the drafting and writing of of the Pre-Qualification Documentations, including Terms of Reference (TOR), PQ Document, Info Memo, Procurement Guidelines, as well as the Press Release;
- Assist in the development of financial and economics analysis for the Tanah Ampo Cruise Terminal Project.
